data.description: Welcome to this enchanting 4-bedroom, 3.5-bathroom Victorian row home, perfectly positioned in the heart of Washington DC's vibrant and desirable area between NOMA and H Street NE. Nestled on a picturesque block, this south-facing property offers a harmonious blend of classic charm and modern comfort. As you enter, you're greeted by beautiful bay front windows that flood the space with natural light, accentuating the freshly painted walls and creating a warm, inviting atmosphere. The main level is highlighted by a stunning dining room space featuring 9-foot ceilings and beautiful hardwood floors. The upper level is comprised of three bedrooms and 2 full bathrooms including a gorgeous primary bedroom space that faces L St. The finished lower level offers the flexibility of having a fourth bedroom, rec room or office. There is also a separate laundry room and full bathroom. Stepping outside, you are within walking distance to a plethora of amenities.  Easy access to The NOMA metro stop, Union Station and Trader Joes.  Union Market, a hub of culinary delights and artisanal shops, is a short stroll away, offering a unique and vibrant experience. The bustling H Street, known for its eclectic mix of dining, entertainment, and shopping, is also conveniently close. Property updates include: New Carrier HVAC system in 2018, New roof in 2019, New refrigerator / freezer in 2020 New hot water heater in 2022, complete basement bath remodel and new fencing in 2023.
